1
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:36,296
If she does anything

2
00:01:36,396 --> 00:01:37,464
wrong,

3
00:01:37,630 --> 00:01:38,865
just tell me anytime.

4
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:39,933
I'll straighten her out.

5
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:42,669
Your senior sister

6
00:01:43,069 --> 00:01:43,903
asked me to bring Senlin

7
00:01:43,903 --> 00:01:45,438
his favorite snacks.

8
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:46,840
I left them in the car.

9
00:01:47,106 --> 00:01:48,041
After the meeting,

10
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:48,842
let's have dinner together.

11
00:01:49,142 --> 00:01:49,509
Okay.

12
00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:50,944
Let me get you some water.

13
00:01:54,747 --> 00:01:55,281
Secretary-General.

14
00:01:55,748 --> 00:01:57,050
Have the members of your academic lineage

15
00:01:57,484 --> 00:01:58,485
always been this close?

16
00:01:58,885 --> 00:01:59,352
Yes.

17
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:01,187
Back in school,

18
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:02,522
I spoiled her too much.

19
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:04,290
At our alumni gatherings,

20
00:02:04,491 --> 00:02:06,025
she never knew when to lend a hand.

21
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:07,560
Look at her now.

22
00:02:08,928 --> 00:02:09,863
She's even learned to

23
00:02:09,929 --> 00:02:11,331
serve tea and water.

24
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:14,334
It seems Dongli Hospital

25
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,169
really trains people well.

26
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:20,773
I'll get back to work, Professor.

27
00:02:21,374 --> 00:02:22,642
Secretary-General, have some tea.

28
00:02:23,943 --> 00:02:24,511
Secretary-General.

29
00:02:24,844 --> 00:02:25,478
The last time we met

30
00:02:25,545 --> 00:02:26,346
was in Hangzhou, right?

31
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:30,016
Yes, yes.

32
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:30,717
Please sit.

33
00:02:31,251 --> 00:02:31,751
Have a seat.

34
00:02:36,289 --> 00:02:38,224
Professor, why did you come

35
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:39,158
to the Heart Failure Branch today?

36
00:02:39,726 --> 00:02:40,760
Zhou Xiaofeng.

37
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:42,295
He invited me.

38
00:02:43,396 --> 00:02:45,632
You're just too stubborn.

39
00:02:45,932 --> 00:02:46,833
If I hadn't come,

40
00:02:47,433 --> 00:02:48,368
I wouldn't have known

41
00:02:48,434 --> 00:02:49,836
they'd been bullying you this badly.

42
00:02:51,070 --> 00:02:52,805
That Sheng Nian really has some nerve.

43
00:02:53,206 --> 00:02:54,240
His mentor, Wang Zhifeng,

44
00:02:54,307 --> 00:02:55,408
is my senior fellow.

45
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:56,809
So the two of you

46
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,845
are indirectly from the same academic lineage.

47
00:03:01,247 --> 00:03:02,882
What did Zhou Xiaofeng tell you?

48
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:04,751
Not much.

49
00:03:05,084 --> 00:03:06,152
He only said

50
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:07,353
Director Sheng

51
00:03:07,487 --> 00:03:09,355
was very demanding of vendors.

52
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:13,359
Zhou Xiaofeng may be quiet,

53
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,727
but he's smart.

54
00:03:15,295 --> 00:03:16,596
He knew to call me.

55
00:03:17,263 --> 00:03:18,131
Some things

56
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:20,633
don't need to be spelled out.

57
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:21,868
Of course I knew

58
00:03:21,968 --> 00:03:23,369
why he asked me to come.

59
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,575
I chose this path myself.

60
00:03:29,275 --> 00:03:30,343
Even if I have to grit my teeth

61
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:31,678
and swallow the pain,

62
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:32,812
I still have to keep going.

63
00:03:34,414 --> 00:03:36,115
Why did he call you?

64
00:03:36,716 --> 00:03:37,050
I...

65
00:03:38,785 --> 00:03:39,986
Now I feel

66
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:40,787
terribly guilty.

67
00:03:40,853 --> 00:03:41,854
I've made you worry.

68
00:03:42,455 --> 00:03:43,022
You...

69
00:03:43,156 --> 00:03:44,290
Why are you being so formal with me?

70
00:03:44,757 --> 00:03:46,593
Even Sun Wukong, on his journey west,

71
00:03:46,793 --> 00:03:48,161
would ask the immortals for help

72
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:48,928
when he met a demon

73
00:03:49,195 --> 00:03:51,197
he couldn't defeat,

74
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:51,931
right?

75
00:03:52,832 --> 00:03:53,633
So

76
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:54,767
turning to your teacher

77
00:03:55,001 --> 00:03:56,135
is nothing to be ashamed of.

78
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:57,570
Besides,

79
00:03:57,837 --> 00:03:59,872
shouldn't Professor Jiang's name

80
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:01,608
carry some weight with Sheng Nian?

81
00:04:03,242 --> 00:04:04,043
Yes, yes.

82
00:04:06,145 --> 00:04:07,247
How is Senlin?

83
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:08,214
He's doing well.

84
00:04:08,514 --> 00:04:09,449
He's gotten taller lately.

85
00:04:09,549 --> 00:04:10,016
Really?

86
00:04:11,484 --> 00:04:12,318
I know

87
00:04:12,785 --> 00:04:14,387
caring for Senlin is hard.

88
00:04:14,687 --> 00:04:15,655
I hope you can

89
00:04:15,655 --> 00:04:16,889
take good care of yourself too.

90
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:19,359
Okay. I will.

91
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:23,429
I heard

92
00:04:23,663 --> 00:04:26,466
Professor Wu at Dongjiang University next door

93
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:28,368
has been working on

94
00:04:28,468 --> 00:04:30,203
gene-editing research,

95
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:32,905
mainly for cardiomyopathy.

96
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:34,274
Apparently,

97
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:35,808
she discovered

98
00:04:35,908 --> 00:04:37,944
a nanoparticle with

99
00:04:38,211 --> 00:04:38,945
a very high transfection efficiency

100
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:40,280
and excellent specificity.

101
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,214
Really?

102
00:04:41,881 --> 00:04:43,316
I heard Professor Wu's team

103
00:04:43,316 --> 00:04:43,950
has already entered

104
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:45,685
the small-animal testing stage.

105
00:04:46,185 --> 00:04:47,453
If the research

106
00:04:47,687 --> 00:04:49,188
continues to advance,

107
00:04:50,156 --> 00:04:51,190
it could be a breakthrough

108
00:04:51,357 --> 00:04:52,525
for Senlin's condition.

109
00:04:53,826 --> 00:04:55,161
It's just unfortunate

110
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:57,130
that Professor Wu is in poor health.

111
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,565
I heard the project

112
00:04:59,565 --> 00:05:01,567
has been recruiting collaborators.

113
00:05:01,934 --> 00:05:03,503
Why don't you ask around?

114
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:04,971
Really?

115
00:05:06,172 --> 00:05:07,907
This could be an important breakthrough.

116
00:05:08,174 --> 00:05:08,841
Exactly.

117
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:09,642
That's why I came to you

118
00:05:09,676 --> 00:05:10,443
as soon as I heard.

119
00:05:10,743 --> 00:05:12,412
Starting from nothing is incredibly hard.

120
00:05:12,512 --> 00:05:13,446
Like your brother said,

121
00:05:13,546 --> 00:05:14,113
it's like

122
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:15,682
pushing a heavy truck by hand.

123
00:05:15,915 --> 00:05:17,150
But now someone has helped us

124
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:18,885
start the engine.

125
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:20,753
If we follow their path

126
00:05:20,753 --> 00:05:21,487
and give it another push,

127
00:05:21,688 --> 00:05:22,689
won't it be much easier?

128
00:05:22,955 --> 00:05:23,322
Right.

129
00:05:23,556 --> 00:05:24,991
This is a great opportunity.

130
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:26,826
I'll contact Professor Wu

131
00:05:26,893 --> 00:05:27,794
as soon as possible,

132
00:05:28,027 --> 00:05:28,995
see when she's available,

133
00:05:29,195 --> 00:05:30,329
and arrange a meeting.

134
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:30,830
Good.

135
00:05:32,031 --> 00:05:32,865
The sooner, the better.

136
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:34,000
Don't let someone else get there first.

137
00:05:35,268 --> 00:05:36,069
I've carefully read

138
00:05:36,135 --> 00:05:36,869
your paper.

139
00:05:37,303 --> 00:05:38,671
The nanoparticle you discovered

140
00:05:38,905 --> 00:05:39,772
can now achieve

141
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:41,507
relatively precise delivery, right?

142
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:43,109
Our preliminary

143
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:45,712
tests in mice

144
00:05:46,045 --> 00:05:48,348
look promising.

145
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:50,683
But we're still far

146
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:51,918
from drawing any conclusions.

147
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:53,553
Much more careful research

148
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:55,455
is needed.

149
00:05:55,788 --> 00:05:56,756
Unfortunately,

150
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,224
two weeks ago,

151
00:05:58,624 --> 00:06:00,693
I was diagnosed with

152
00:06:00,727 --> 00:06:01,994
advanced pancreatic cancer.

153
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:03,930
The median survival time

154
00:06:04,864 --> 00:06:05,998
is six months to a year.

155
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:09,202
I very, very much

156
00:06:10,403 --> 00:06:12,805
hope someone can take over

157
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:14,507
and finish the work I can't complete.

158
00:06:15,108 --> 00:06:16,275
But this road

159
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:17,643
will be far harder

160
00:06:17,677 --> 00:06:19,045
than you imagine.

161
00:06:19,312 --> 00:06:20,947
All three of you

162
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:22,281
are young and accomplished.

163
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:24,050
Why come here to suffer?

164
00:06:28,855 --> 00:06:29,422
Professor Wu,

165
00:06:29,789 --> 00:06:31,090
we thought this through carefully

166
00:06:31,124 --> 00:06:31,958
before coming to you.

167
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:34,327
We've seen too many

168
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,328
cardiomyopathy patients

169
00:06:35,928 --> 00:06:37,196
progress to end-stage heart failure

170
00:06:38,664 --> 00:06:39,866
without access to

171
00:06:40,266 --> 00:06:40,767
heart transplantation

172
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,068
or an artificial heart.

173
00:06:45,204 --> 00:06:46,005
As doctors,

174
00:06:47,974 --> 00:06:49,242
we truly hate

175
00:06:49,709 --> 00:06:51,210
that sense of helplessness.

176
00:06:52,145 --> 00:06:52,745
Professor Wu,

177
00:06:54,113 --> 00:06:55,948
I have a five-year-old child.

178
00:06:56,449 --> 00:06:57,950
When he was just over two,

179
00:06:58,551 --> 00:07:00,253
he was diagnosed with restrictive cardiomyopathy.

180
00:07:00,887 --> 00:07:02,588
It was caused by a genetic mutation.

181
00:07:02,989 --> 00:07:03,689
So

182
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:05,425
I do have a personal motive.

183
00:07:06,159 --> 00:07:07,693
But please believe

184
00:07:08,161 --> 00:07:09,695
in my drive and sincerity,

185
00:07:10,229 --> 00:07:11,564
and in our sincerity as well.

186
00:07:13,366 --> 00:07:15,067
We also have

187
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:16,736
a colleague in Cardiac Surgery.

188
00:07:17,303 --> 00:07:19,639
His father, brother, and nephew

189
00:07:20,239 --> 00:07:22,208
all died of dilated cardiomyopathy.

190
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:26,012
He himself has an incompletely penetrant

191
00:07:26,078 --> 00:07:27,113
monogenic disorder.

192
00:07:27,547 --> 00:07:28,648
He was tested

193
00:07:29,048 --> 00:07:30,583
and carries the pathogenic gene.

194
00:07:31,484 --> 00:07:32,451
He's a gifted

195
00:07:32,451 --> 00:07:33,252
surgeon.

196
00:07:33,719 --> 00:07:34,387
In Cardiac Surgery?

197
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:35,888
His surname is Lin?

198
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:36,556
Yes.

199
00:07:37,056 --> 00:07:38,357
Professor Cao's student?

200
00:07:39,192 --> 00:07:39,559
Yes.

201
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:40,793
We've all heard

202
00:07:40,927 --> 00:07:42,295
about his family.

203
00:07:42,862 --> 00:07:44,797
Generation after generation,

204
00:07:44,931 --> 00:07:45,765
we researchers

205
00:07:45,998 --> 00:07:47,133
have kept searching,

206
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,569
hoping

207
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,404
to stop tragedies like this

208
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:53,806
at their source.

209
00:08:00,446 --> 00:08:02,048
I don't doubt

210
00:08:02,081 --> 00:08:03,149
your sincerity.

211
00:08:03,749 --> 00:08:05,151
But I have to

212
00:08:05,251 --> 00:08:06,152
be honest with you.

213
00:08:07,253 --> 00:08:08,287
This project

214
00:08:08,487 --> 00:08:09,722
has reached the point

215
00:08:10,089 --> 00:08:12,391
where almost no funding remains.

216
00:08:12,925 --> 00:08:14,961
So it would have to be re-established.

217
00:08:15,294 --> 00:08:17,330
That means not only manpower,

218
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:19,232
but also a site and funding.

219
00:08:19,565 --> 00:08:21,534
I suggest you think it through again.

220
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:23,803
None of us needs to decide in a hurry.

221
00:08:26,405 --> 00:08:26,839
First,

222
00:08:27,607 --> 00:08:28,774
we should apply to our hospital

223
00:08:28,841 --> 00:08:29,509
and get approval.

224
00:08:30,643 --> 00:08:32,011
Continuing a series of related studies

225
00:08:32,211 --> 00:08:33,112
should be easier than

226
00:08:33,112 --> 00:08:33,913
starting a completely new one.

227
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:34,347
Right.

228
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:34,881
Leave that to me.

229
00:08:35,481 --> 00:08:36,682
I heard our hospital's laboratories

230
00:08:36,682 --> 00:08:37,350
are in high demand.

231
00:08:37,383 --> 00:08:38,351
Many people apply,

232
00:08:38,751 --> 00:08:39,519
and even qualified projects

233
00:08:39,552 --> 00:08:40,453
have to queue in advance.

234
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:41,520
I'll look into it.

235
00:08:43,155 --> 00:08:45,358
I'll also ask around

236
00:08:45,424 --> 00:08:46,225
and see whether any companies

237
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:47,560
are willing to sponsor us.

238
00:08:48,995 --> 00:08:50,096
As for laboratories,

239
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:51,197
there are actually

240
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,398
many research institutions outside the hospital

241
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:53,966
that rent out lab space.

242
00:08:56,736 --> 00:08:57,670
I need to get back to the hospital.

243
00:08:58,671 --> 00:08:59,038
I'm leaving.

244
00:08:59,672 --> 00:09:00,306
Take care.

245
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:03,409
I think deep down,

246
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:04,510
she still thinks about Lin Yi.

247
00:09:06,145 --> 00:09:07,480
Her eyes give her away.

248
00:09:07,914 --> 00:09:08,347
Right?

249
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:15,488
Director Zhou.

250
00:09:16,322 --> 00:09:17,423
Doing good without taking credit, huh?

251
00:09:18,424 --> 00:09:19,091
What do you mean?

252
00:09:20,526 --> 00:09:21,627
Professor Jiang told me everything.

253
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:27,533
Thanks to you,

254
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:28,601
Director Sheng

255
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:29,769
hasn't given me any trouble these past two days.

256
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:31,571
That was because of you.

257
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:32,672
Professor Jiang's name

258
00:09:34,607 --> 00:09:37,009
still carries weight.

259
00:09:37,209 --> 00:09:38,311
Director Zhou is truly farsighted.

260
00:09:39,278 --> 00:09:40,813
Before long, you'll become

261
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:41,881
a powerful figure

262
00:09:41,948 --> 00:09:43,449
who shelters all of us juniors

263
00:09:43,883 --> 00:09:45,184
and steadies the whole situation.

264
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:45,484
Hello.

265
00:09:45,551 --> 00:09:46,986
Are you Cardiology Whirlwind?

266
00:09:47,687 --> 00:09:48,688
Can we take a photo with you?

267
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:50,022
We all really like you.

268
00:09:50,156 --> 00:09:51,390
We follow your account.

269
00:09:52,892 --> 00:09:53,225
Sure.

270
00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:54,360
Of course.

271
00:09:54,493 --> 00:09:55,394
Thank you. Thank you.

272
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:56,262
Please.

273
00:09:57,563 --> 00:09:58,831
Let's do that gesture.

274
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:01,133
Okay, let's record a video.

275
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,768
One, two, three. Start.

276
00:10:04,370 --> 00:10:04,770
Done.

277
00:10:05,204 --> 00:10:05,972
Thank you. Thank you.

278
00:10:05,972 --> 00:10:07,173
My mother likes you too.

279
00:10:08,207 --> 00:10:09,008
Remember to keep posting.

280
00:10:09,709 --> 00:10:10,142
Thank you.

281
00:10:10,242 --> 00:10:10,643
Bye.

282
00:10:14,146 --> 00:10:15,281
A mom fan.

283
00:10:15,681 --> 00:10:16,649
Impressive.

284
00:10:19,485 --> 00:10:20,119
You're famous now.

285
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:21,454
You won't forget me, will you?

286
00:10:25,925 --> 00:10:26,425
I'm leaving.

287
00:10:26,926 --> 00:10:27,393
Be safe.

288
00:10:29,495 --> 00:10:30,196
Little Whirlwind.

289
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:33,165
Thanks.

290
00:10:49,448 --> 00:10:50,683
You're a department director.

291
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:52,685
Why insist on picking on a salesperson?

292
00:10:52,685 --> 00:10:53,285
Why insist on picking on a salesperson?

293
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:54,387
I didn't.

294
00:10:55,721 --> 00:10:56,956
I only asked her to deliver supplies

295
00:10:57,023 --> 00:10:57,590
and provide procedural support.

296
00:10:57,623 --> 00:10:58,557
I didn't do anything to her.

297
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:00,826
If you hadn't,

298
00:11:02,294 --> 00:11:03,195
would Jiang Wei have called

299
00:11:03,195 --> 00:11:04,063
me personally?

300
00:11:05,931 --> 00:11:06,966
That junior of mine

301
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,868
is famously protective of her people.

302
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:10,569
Why provoke her?

303
00:11:11,203 --> 00:11:12,371
It was such a small matter.

304
00:11:12,438 --> 00:11:14,440
Was it worth calling you over?

305
00:11:14,807 --> 00:11:16,108
I really need to remind you:

306
00:11:16,709 --> 00:11:18,444
stay out of this kind of mess.

307
00:11:19,145 --> 00:11:20,646
A little impatience can ruin a great plan.

308
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:23,015
Right now, the most important thing

309
00:11:23,082 --> 00:11:24,116
is to focus your energy

310
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,052
on what truly matters.

311
00:11:26,385 --> 00:11:27,153
As the saying goes,

312
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:29,889
a general on the march

313
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:32,091
doesn't chase rabbits.

314
00:11:32,425 --> 00:11:33,793
Your hybrid procedure

315
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:35,361
a while ago

316
00:11:35,928 --> 00:11:37,329
was quite successful.

317
00:11:37,763 --> 00:11:39,331
You should seize this opportunity

318
00:11:39,665 --> 00:11:41,434
to further raise

319
00:11:42,601 --> 00:11:43,602
All right, Professor. I understand.

320
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:44,670
I'll be careful.

321
00:12:15,935 --> 00:12:16,802
The patient has torsades de pointes.

322
00:12:16,802 --> 00:12:17,603
Prepare to defibrillate.

323
00:12:17,636 --> 00:12:17,970
Understood.

324
00:12:19,105 --> 00:12:20,072
Two grams of magnesium sulfate IV push.

325
00:12:20,106 --> 00:12:21,073
Two grams of magnesium sulfate IV push.

326
00:12:33,452 --> 00:12:34,286
Her potassium and magnesium are low.

327
00:12:34,386 --> 00:12:35,754
It may be related to an electrolyte imbalance.

328
00:12:36,288 --> 00:12:37,156
Find a way to correct it.

329
00:12:40,292 --> 00:12:42,128
The ventricular repolarization interval is prolonged.

330
00:12:43,996 --> 00:12:45,164
Was she given azithromycin?

331
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:45,798
No.

332
00:12:46,532 --> 00:12:48,234
None of the drugs that may induce

333
00:12:48,234 --> 00:12:49,335
prolonged ventricular repolarization were used.

334
00:12:49,902 --> 00:12:50,903
Could it be related

335
00:12:51,036 --> 00:12:52,505
to her cardiac trauma

336
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:54,373
and the stress of surgery?

337
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,309
Possibly. Let's keep watching.

338
00:13:05,918 --> 00:13:06,485
She's in ventricular tachycardia again.

339
00:13:06,685 --> 00:13:07,153
The defibrillator.

340
00:13:09,922 --> 00:13:10,923
Defibrillator, now.

341
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:17,396
Sorry. Sorry.

342
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:24,470
Based on her current symptoms

343
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:25,638
and ECG,

344
00:13:25,905 --> 00:13:26,438
this is most likely

345
00:13:26,438 --> 00:13:27,640
long QT syndrome,

346
00:13:28,574 --> 00:13:29,675
or LQTS.

347
00:13:30,676 --> 00:13:31,677
Abnormal cardiac electrical activity

348
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:32,812
is causing the arrhythmia.

349
00:13:36,048 --> 00:13:37,883
We'd never heard

350
00:13:38,584 --> 00:13:40,119
that she had heart problems.

351
00:13:41,187 --> 00:13:42,521
Her physical exams were normal too.

352
00:13:43,956 --> 00:13:44,490
Could...

353
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:47,593
could this have been caused by the injury?

354
00:13:53,232 --> 00:13:54,733
It's most likely unrelated to the trauma.

355
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:57,636
Has she ever fainted before?

356
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:00,573
Yes, yes.

357
00:14:01,106 --> 00:14:02,474
She fainted twice

358
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:03,842
in college,

359
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:06,812
but the campus doctor said it was hypoglycemia.

360
00:14:07,079 --> 00:14:08,914
Right. She may take after me.

361
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:10,115
I have low blood sugar too.

362
00:14:10,883 --> 00:14:11,850
Have you fainted as well?

363
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:13,252
Well...

364
00:14:13,953 --> 00:14:14,787
last month,

365
00:14:15,321 --> 00:14:17,456
I got up at night

366
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:19,225
and maybe stood too quickly.

367
00:14:19,391 --> 00:14:20,226
Then I suddenly

368
00:14:20,226 --> 00:14:21,493
collapsed to the floor.

369
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:24,330
I recovered on my own later.

370
00:14:25,264 --> 00:14:26,265
We recommend

371
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:27,600
genetic testing for her.

372
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,235
Her parents and brother

373
00:14:29,401 --> 00:14:30,736
should ideally be tested too.

374
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,471
Long QT syndrome

375
00:14:32,504 --> 00:14:34,073
is associated with genetic mutations.

376
00:14:34,473 --> 00:14:36,609
So you should also register

377
00:14:37,142 --> 00:14:38,544
with Cardiology for an examination.

378
00:14:41,013 --> 00:14:42,548
These arrhythmias can occur

379
00:14:42,848 --> 00:14:44,149
during exercise

380
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:45,517
or emotional excitement,

381
00:14:45,851 --> 00:14:47,453
while sleeping,

382
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,355
or even because of sudden noise.

383
00:14:49,688 --> 00:14:51,156
Both times Yiyi fainted,

384
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:52,491
there was a sudden sound.

385
00:14:54,927 --> 00:14:56,028
Doctor,

386
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:58,063
do you mean

387
00:14:58,631 --> 00:14:59,598
this condition

388
00:15:03,769 --> 00:15:05,237
is congenital?

389
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:12,912
Not necessarily.

390
00:15:13,479 --> 00:15:14,647
Some cases are congenital.

391
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:16,115
Others

392
00:15:16,248 --> 00:15:17,583
may be caused by electrolyte disturbances

393
00:15:17,716 --> 00:15:18,851
or medication.

394
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:20,352
Further testing is needed

395
00:15:20,486 --> 00:15:21,253
to confirm it.

396
00:15:42,207 --> 00:15:43,008
Yan Yiyi's family?

397
00:15:45,077 --> 00:15:45,678
What's wrong?

398
00:15:46,745 --> 00:15:47,346
Dr. Du,

399
00:15:52,918 --> 00:15:55,154
I just looked it up online.

400
00:15:56,855 --> 00:15:57,556
It's okay.

401
00:15:58,624 --> 00:15:59,525
Is Yiyi's condition

402
00:16:00,326 --> 00:16:01,627
very serious?

403
00:16:02,961 --> 00:16:04,196
If she begins

404
00:16:04,263 --> 00:16:05,064
standardized treatment now,

405
00:16:05,364 --> 00:16:06,632
the prognosis is quite good.

406
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,134
Don't be too anxious.

407
00:16:10,269 --> 00:16:11,036
But this condition

408
00:16:12,204 --> 00:16:13,472
can be inherited, right?

409
00:16:16,408 --> 00:16:17,443
There is a possibility.

410
00:16:19,011 --> 00:16:19,845
If you want children

411
00:16:19,845 --> 00:16:20,713
in the future,

412
00:16:20,946 --> 00:16:21,847
even if her condition

413
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,115
is caused by a genetic mutation,

414
00:16:23,682 --> 00:16:24,450
you can try

415
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:25,517
preimplantation genetic testing.

416
00:16:25,751 --> 00:16:26,552
It can largely prevent

417
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:27,653
the next generation from being affected.

418
00:16:29,521 --> 00:16:29,922
Really?

419
00:16:32,758 --> 00:16:33,692
We were originally

420
00:16:33,926 --> 00:16:35,561
planning to marry this National Day.

421
00:16:38,430 --> 00:16:39,198
Thank you, Dr. Du.

422
00:16:45,070 --> 00:16:45,437
Director Lin.

423
00:16:50,809 --> 00:16:51,677
How long are you going to keep watching?

424
00:16:53,645 --> 00:16:54,113
Director.

425
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:57,883
He looks like he's ready to give up.

426
00:16:58,350 --> 00:16:59,184
What does that have to do with you?

427
00:17:00,552 --> 00:17:01,587
And you know about PGT?

428
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:02,287
Are you an expert now?

429
00:17:02,988 --> 00:17:03,622
No, Director.

430
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:04,823
I just think genetics

431
00:17:04,923 --> 00:17:05,924
isn't so absolute.

432
00:17:06,325 --> 00:17:07,126
Technology is advancing

433
00:17:07,126 --> 00:17:07,826
so quickly.

434
00:17:08,127 --> 00:17:08,827
Maybe one day

435
00:17:08,894 --> 00:17:09,595
we'll overcome it.

436
00:17:09,795 --> 00:17:10,529
Then you do it.

437
00:17:10,796 --> 00:17:11,330
Me?

438
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:14,600
I can't.

439
00:17:14,933 --> 00:17:15,768
But Professor Fang can.

440
00:17:16,568 --> 00:17:17,636
Professor Fang and Director Xiaofeng

441
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:18,971
have been running themselves ragged

442
00:17:19,071 --> 00:17:20,005
for this genetics project.

443
00:17:22,574 --> 00:17:23,375
Didn't you know?

444
00:17:24,843 --> 00:17:25,811
How do you know everything?

445
00:17:26,945 --> 00:17:28,080
Are you Dongli's rumor hotline?

446
00:17:40,159 --> 00:17:40,692
Head Nurse.

447
00:17:41,493 --> 00:17:42,127
Director Lin.

448
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:44,196
This item,

449
00:17:44,263 --> 00:17:45,130
please give it to

450
00:17:45,931 --> 00:17:46,365
Dr. Fang.

451
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:49,368
No problem.

452
00:17:50,436 --> 00:17:53,038
Intensive care training enrollment receipt.

453
00:17:53,639 --> 00:17:54,706
She applied last year,

454
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,175
and finally got in this year.

455
00:17:58,076 --> 00:17:58,610
Last year?

456
00:17:59,278 --> 00:18:00,045
When last year?

457
00:18:00,312 --> 00:18:01,313
Last October.

458
00:18:01,814 --> 00:18:03,515
For some reason, she missed it.

459
00:18:05,317 --> 00:18:05,884
Head Nurse,

460
00:18:07,886 --> 00:18:09,988
I'll give it to her myself.

461
00:18:12,324 --> 00:18:12,825
Thank you.

462
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:13,592
You're welcome.

463
00:18:46,024 --> 00:18:47,359
A package for you was sent home.

464
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:50,929
Thanks.

465
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:56,802
You're going to Critical Care Medicine

466
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:57,603
for training?

467
00:18:59,304 --> 00:18:59,671
Yes.

468
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:01,173
The head nurse said

469
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,474
you had an opportunity last year,

470
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:03,876
but missed it.

471
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:07,846
I was too busy then,

472
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:09,281
and didn't get around to it.

473
00:19:10,349 --> 00:19:11,250
At the time, Xiaorui had

474
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:11,917
a CRT-D implanted,

475
00:19:13,185 --> 00:19:14,086
and I was traveling for surgeries.

476
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:16,288
You were the one caring for him.

477
00:19:17,589 --> 00:19:18,590
I never knew

478
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:21,126
you had sacrificed so much.

479
00:19:27,866 --> 00:19:28,767
It's all in the past.

480
00:19:31,203 --> 00:19:31,637
Thanks.

481
00:19:32,204 --> 00:19:33,505
I'll change the delivery address later.

482
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:45,851
How did

483
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:46,919
long QT syndrome suddenly appear?

484
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:50,756
Her previous physical exams

485
00:19:50,789 --> 00:19:51,924
were all normal.

486
00:19:55,627 --> 00:19:56,295
Routine physical exams

487
00:19:56,295 --> 00:19:57,362
don't check that thoroughly.

488
00:20:01,066 --> 00:20:01,934
Tang Yuyao.

489
00:20:06,772 --> 00:20:07,839
Let's break up.

490
00:20:17,115 --> 00:20:17,916
Your family

491
00:20:18,483 --> 00:20:19,151
already disapproved

492
00:20:19,284 --> 00:20:20,118
of us being together.

493
00:20:20,852 --> 00:20:22,688
You're the only son in a big family,

494
00:20:23,488 --> 00:20:24,590
and I kept you here in Dongjiang.

495
00:20:26,358 --> 00:20:27,125
Your parents

496
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:29,194
and grandmother have always resented it.

497
00:20:33,432 --> 00:20:35,233
Now I've been diagnosed with this condition,

498
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,637
and no one knows what the future holds.

499
00:20:44,509 --> 00:20:45,677
I don't want to burden you.

500
00:20:49,314 --> 00:20:50,649
Let's part on good terms.

501
00:20:53,952 --> 00:20:54,786
Are you finished?

502
00:21:01,526 --> 00:21:02,094
Right now,

503
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:03,895
the most important thing

504
00:21:04,162 --> 00:21:05,063
is not to overthink.

505
00:21:05,230 --> 00:21:06,265
Focus on getting better.

506
00:21:07,132 --> 00:21:08,000
I'm not overthinking.

507
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:09,001
I'm serious.

508
00:21:25,517 --> 00:21:26,084
Tangtang,

509
00:21:26,551 --> 00:21:28,320
a relationship weighed down by guilt

510
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:31,990
is like a paper boat.

511
00:21:34,426 --> 00:21:36,094
No matter how carefully you protect it,

512
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:39,064
it can't withstand even a little wind or rain.

513
00:21:41,466 --> 00:21:43,201
I don't want our relationship

514
00:21:44,069 --> 00:21:45,837
to carry something this heavy.

515
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:50,609
Yiyi,

516
00:21:50,676 --> 00:21:51,610
I've never thought about breaking up.

517
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:52,144
Tangtang,

518
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:56,348
while there's still time,

519
00:21:57,115 --> 00:21:57,683
leave.

520
00:22:02,688 --> 00:22:04,523
I've been very happy

521
00:22:06,792 --> 00:22:07,626
these past two years with you.

522
00:22:11,596 --> 00:22:12,230
Thank you.

523
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:56,308
If you're not answering, stop calling.

524
00:23:02,948 --> 00:23:04,483
Why has that kid disappeared?

525
00:23:05,083 --> 00:23:06,151
Could something have happened?

526
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,187
What could happen to him?

527
00:23:10,989 --> 00:23:12,791
He probably despises Yiyi now that she's sick

528
00:23:13,625 --> 00:23:14,760
and wants out.

529
00:23:17,329 --> 00:23:18,830
Tangtang is a decent kid.

530
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:20,732
He wouldn't do that.

531
00:23:23,168 --> 00:23:24,636
True love shows itself in hardship.

532
00:23:25,804 --> 00:23:26,671
Only when hardship comes

533
00:23:27,005 --> 00:23:28,840
can you see someone's true heart.

534
00:23:29,908 --> 00:23:31,042
All right. Stop calling.

535
00:23:32,944 --> 00:23:33,912
Have you heard?

536
00:23:34,346 --> 00:23:35,747
Yan Yiyi's boyfriend

537
00:23:36,148 --> 00:23:37,015
disappeared.

538
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:39,951
Yeah. He vanished.

539
00:23:41,553 --> 00:23:42,654
Human nature ultimately

540
00:23:42,721 --> 00:23:43,955
can't withstand a test.

541
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:46,224
No need to be so pessimistic.

542
00:23:46,491 --> 00:23:47,726
I think this matter

543
00:23:48,026 --> 00:23:49,828
depends on your position

544
00:23:50,028 --> 00:23:51,129
and perspective.

545
00:23:51,329 --> 00:23:52,164
Whatever decision

546
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:53,665
he makes,

547
00:23:53,832 --> 00:23:54,599
it's understandable.

548
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:55,734
Think about it.

549
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:57,402
Long QT syndrome

550
00:23:57,469 --> 00:23:58,203
is no small matter.

551
00:23:58,437 --> 00:23:59,404
It affects an entire lifetime

552
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:00,972
and may even affect future children.

553
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:03,108
Besides, how old is he?

554
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:04,476
Only in his twenties. Still so young.

555
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:06,478
Since ancient times,

556
00:24:06,645 --> 00:24:07,679
love

557
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,147
has always been the most fragile thing.

558
00:24:09,347 --> 00:24:09,881
I agree.

559
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:10,449
Brother Dong,

560
00:24:10,482 --> 00:24:11,483
I don't agree with that.

561
00:24:11,716 --> 00:24:13,084
It only means

562
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:13,985
their love wasn't deep enough.

563
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,121
But I heard Yan Yiyi

564
00:24:16,254 --> 00:24:17,389
was the one who proposed breaking up.

565
00:24:17,722 --> 00:24:20,091
Then isn't it normal that he disappeared?

566
00:24:20,792 --> 00:24:21,760
No wonder you're single.

567
00:24:21,927 --> 00:24:22,828
Sometimes when someone says "break up,"

568
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:24,196
they don't really mean it.

569
00:24:24,229 --> 00:24:24,496
Right?

570
00:24:24,696 --> 00:24:25,730
What if she was only hurt

571
00:24:25,764 --> 00:24:26,431
and upset,

572
00:24:26,598 --> 00:24:27,833
waiting for him to comfort her?

573
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:29,000
At the very least,

574
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,236
he should have fought for the relationship.

575
00:24:47,786 --> 00:24:48,920
Emotional trauma

576
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,755
can affect her recovery.

577
00:24:50,889 --> 00:24:52,424
What she needs most now

578
00:24:52,557 --> 00:24:54,526
is encouragement and support from her family.

579
00:24:58,597 --> 00:25:00,165
Why does our Yiyi

580
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:03,001
have to suffer so much?

581
00:25:23,388 --> 00:25:24,823
Doctor, may I ask

582
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,124
where I sign this?

583
00:25:26,224 --> 00:25:27,225
Over here. Come with me.

584
00:26:09,334 --> 00:26:09,935
Who are you?

585
00:26:10,669 --> 00:26:11,269
How did you get in here?

586
00:26:11,670 --> 00:26:13,038
I... I...

587
00:26:13,104 --> 00:26:14,306
You can't be in here. Get out.

588
00:26:14,706 --> 00:26:15,674
No, wait.

589
00:26:16,641 --> 00:26:17,208
Don't run.

590
00:26:17,242 --> 00:26:17,542
Quick.

591
00:26:17,609 --> 00:26:18,343
Someone broke in.

592
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:19,144
Get out. Stop running.

593
00:26:19,511 --> 00:26:20,111
Stop right there.

594
00:26:22,147 --> 00:26:22,681
Sister Yalan,

595
00:26:23,114 --> 00:26:23,949
have you heard?

596
00:26:24,449 --> 00:26:25,116
A thief broke into

597
00:26:25,116 --> 00:26:25,784
the general ICU.

598
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:28,053
What thief?

599
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:29,387
It was a misunderstanding.

600
00:26:32,290 --> 00:26:33,358
Sister Beibei told me.

601
00:26:33,758 --> 00:26:35,827
It was Yan Yiyi's brother.

602
00:26:36,695 --> 00:26:38,029
That man

603
00:26:38,063 --> 00:26:39,464
is really strange.

604
00:26:39,798 --> 00:26:41,032
In broad daylight,

605
00:26:41,232 --> 00:26:42,067
he could have visited normally,

606
00:26:42,367 --> 00:26:42,934
but he didn't.

607
00:26:43,568 --> 00:26:45,103
Instead, he waited until late at night,

608
00:26:45,503 --> 00:26:46,705
when everything was quiet,

609
00:26:47,072 --> 00:26:47,872
and secretly slipped in alone.

610
00:26:48,039 --> 00:26:48,907
and secretly slipped in alone.

611
00:26:49,574 --> 00:26:50,208
I heard

612
00:26:50,208 --> 00:26:50,809
several male doctors

613
00:26:50,842 --> 00:26:52,277
from the general ICU

614
00:26:52,410 --> 00:26:53,411
had to pin him down.

615
00:26:53,745 --> 00:26:55,213
They thought he was a thief.

616
00:26:56,314 --> 00:26:57,349
Something like that really happened?

617
00:26:59,050 --> 00:26:59,584
Maybe he still

618
00:26:59,684 --> 00:27:00,552
wanted to see his sister.

619
00:27:01,553 --> 00:27:02,387
Probably.

620
00:27:02,887 --> 00:27:03,722
But no matter what the doctors asked,

621
00:27:03,855 --> 00:27:04,656
he wouldn't say.

622
00:27:05,190 --> 00:27:05,724
So

623
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:06,925
they could only escort him out.

624
00:27:10,228 --> 00:27:11,229
Excuse me,

625
00:27:11,363 --> 00:27:13,064
how do I get to the sixth floor?

626
00:27:13,865 --> 00:27:15,834
Have you been inside that ICU?

627
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:22,007
What's it like in there?

628
00:27:25,677 --> 00:27:26,911
Why are you still here?

629
00:27:27,012 --> 00:27:27,612
Go back and rest.

630
00:27:27,679 --> 00:27:28,446
Go on. Get some rest.

631
00:27:28,713 --> 00:27:29,314
I'm going back.

632
00:27:30,048 --> 00:27:30,749
Call us if you need anything.

633
00:27:30,949 --> 00:27:31,216
Okay.

634
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:52,170
Yan Chunjing.

635
00:28:12,323 --> 00:28:12,991
Wait a moment.

636
00:28:17,996 --> 00:28:19,464
Hello, Dr. Xiaoran.

637
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:20,198
Is now okay?

638
00:28:20,799 --> 00:28:21,666
Yes, now is fine.

639
00:28:27,238 --> 00:28:28,173
She's asleep.

640
00:28:51,963 --> 00:28:52,664
That's for oxygen.

641
00:28:55,767 --> 00:28:57,001
Everything is stable now.

642
00:28:57,202 --> 00:28:58,069
Don't worry too much.

643
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,707
Before falling asleep, she said she missed her brother.

644
00:29:17,822 --> 00:29:18,389
We should hang up now.

645
00:29:19,290 --> 00:29:20,358
Don't disturb her rest.

646
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:23,228
Thank you, Dr. Xiaoran.

647
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:24,329
I'll hang up first.

648
00:29:24,829 --> 00:29:25,597
Okay. No problem.

649
00:29:42,947 --> 00:29:43,715
Dr. Fang.

650
00:29:44,315 --> 00:29:45,350
Did I wake you?

651
00:29:48,753 --> 00:29:49,721
I slept too long.

652
00:29:50,054 --> 00:29:51,156
My body clock is completely off.

653
00:29:58,163 --> 00:29:59,130
Are you okay?

654
00:30:02,033 --> 00:30:03,334
When I was four,

655
00:30:05,904 --> 00:30:06,771
I became seriously ill

656
00:30:13,545 --> 00:30:15,213
with aplastic anemia.

657
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:18,783
My sister was born

658
00:30:18,917 --> 00:30:20,652
to be an HLA-matched sibling donor for me.

659
00:30:23,755 --> 00:30:25,924
She gave me a cord blood transplant,

660
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:28,993
and that's why I survived.

661
00:30:30,528 --> 00:30:31,329
Yiyi

662
00:30:34,566 --> 00:30:35,366
is smart,

663
00:30:36,434 --> 00:30:37,402
does well in school,

664
00:30:39,871 --> 00:30:40,772
and has a good personality.

665
00:30:42,307 --> 00:30:42,974
Unlike me.

666
00:30:43,675 --> 00:30:44,676
From the moment I was born,

667
00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:47,312
I became a burden to the whole family.

668
00:30:50,315 --> 00:30:52,483
Money, treatment,

669
00:30:55,386 --> 00:30:57,255
and constant careful protection—

670
00:30:57,889 --> 00:30:59,524
they gave me all their focus

671
00:31:00,024 --> 00:31:01,559
and attention.

672
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:04,596
No one could scold or criticize me.

673
00:31:05,396 --> 00:31:06,331
Even after something this serious happened,

674
00:31:06,331 --> 00:31:07,265
not a single person

675
00:31:07,565 --> 00:31:09,334
blamed me.

676
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:12,170
Only after I grew up did I understand

677
00:31:14,405 --> 00:31:16,074
I was born because of my brother.

678
00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:20,044
So deep down,

679
00:31:21,145 --> 00:31:22,714
he felt he owed me a great deal.

680
00:31:23,748 --> 00:31:25,450
It took me a long time

681
00:31:26,484 --> 00:31:27,986
to make our relationship

682
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:30,488
feel like that of ordinary siblings,

683
00:31:31,656 --> 00:31:32,824
teasing each other

684
00:31:33,825 --> 00:31:34,692
and joking around.

685
00:31:38,563 --> 00:31:39,731
But this accident

686
00:31:41,733 --> 00:31:43,434
brought everything back to the beginning.

687
00:31:49,274 --> 00:31:49,774
Look.

688
00:31:51,709 --> 00:31:53,478
He still refuses to come see me.

689
00:31:55,847 --> 00:31:57,115
I want to see her.

690
00:32:00,184 --> 00:32:01,753
But I don't want her to see me.

691
00:32:02,854 --> 00:32:03,855
I only wanted to sneak in

692
00:32:03,855 --> 00:32:04,889
and look at her from a distance.

693
00:32:05,323 --> 00:32:06,824
She's already in so much pain.

694
00:32:09,627 --> 00:32:11,529
And I was the one who hurt her.

695
00:32:15,233 --> 00:32:16,267
I don't want her

696
00:32:16,567 --> 00:32:18,603
to pretend to be strong in front of me

697
00:32:19,604 --> 00:32:21,606
and say she is fine and doing well,

698
00:32:25,076 --> 00:32:26,344
and that she's no longer angry with me.

699
00:32:32,317 --> 00:32:33,518
You're overthinking it.

700
00:32:43,227 --> 00:32:44,595
Right where you're sitting,

701
00:32:47,432 --> 00:32:48,199
I once tried to kill myself.

702
00:32:52,704 --> 00:32:53,771
At the time,

703
00:33:01,679 --> 00:33:03,014
I had lost

704
00:33:03,247 --> 00:33:04,015
the most important person in my life.

705
00:33:12,523 --> 00:33:12,990
You don't need to fasten it, right?

706
00:33:12,990 --> 00:33:13,891
Yours is broken.

707
00:33:14,092 --> 00:33:15,193
Here, sit in mine.

708
00:33:16,627 --> 00:33:17,028
Come on.

709
00:33:19,330 --> 00:33:21,065
Buckle my wife in.

710
00:33:31,509 --> 00:33:33,010
In this world, apart from life and death,

711
00:33:33,010 --> 00:33:34,045
nothing is truly that serious.

712
00:33:37,348 --> 00:33:38,016
Truly, nothing.

713
00:33:40,985 --> 00:33:42,553
What you're talking about isn't a big deal.

714
00:33:45,356 --> 00:33:47,025
You're very lucky, you know?

715
00:33:48,493 --> 00:33:49,994
Your sister is still alive,

716
00:33:52,764 --> 00:33:54,832
and your family is still with you.

717
00:33:58,503 --> 00:33:59,404
I envy you.

718
00:34:02,073 --> 00:34:03,241
Someone once told me

719
00:34:09,313 --> 00:34:10,548
that when you want to see someone,

720
00:34:11,682 --> 00:34:13,184
you should go see them right away.

721
00:34:15,653 --> 00:34:18,222
Whether they're crying or smiling,

722
00:34:24,529 --> 00:34:25,329
go see her.

723
00:34:30,401 --> 00:34:31,369
I know too well

724
00:34:33,104 --> 00:34:34,972
how much weight my brother carries.

725
00:34:39,343 --> 00:34:41,245
And I know how hard

726
00:34:43,047 --> 00:34:44,048
I worked before.

727
00:34:51,055 --> 00:34:53,724
So I don't want Tangtang and me

728
00:34:55,092 --> 00:34:56,928
to fall into the same kind of relationship.

729
00:35:07,238 --> 00:35:08,106
This is fine.

730
00:35:09,907 --> 00:35:10,708
Maybe it's better this way.

731
00:35:15,112 --> 00:35:15,947
I understand.

732
00:35:17,248 --> 00:35:19,183
Don't put such a heavy burden on yourself.

733
00:35:22,286 --> 00:35:23,721
Both your body

734
00:35:24,055 --> 00:35:25,223
and your brother's heart

735
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:27,725
will slowly heal.

736
00:35:30,194 --> 00:35:31,596
Even where you cannot see him,

737
00:35:32,396 --> 00:35:33,130
he's watching over you

738
00:35:33,197 --> 00:35:34,132
in his own way.

739
00:35:38,402 --> 00:35:39,303
Like this?

740
00:36:14,872 --> 00:36:16,107
Dad. Mom.

741
00:36:17,608 --> 00:36:18,609
I... I...

742
00:36:19,944 --> 00:36:22,813
I want to see Yiyi.

743
00:36:52,243 --> 00:36:53,311
Yiyi is in Bed 11,

744
00:36:53,711 --> 00:36:54,145
over there.

745
00:37:03,287 --> 00:37:04,055
I hate you.

746
00:37:06,157 --> 00:37:07,158
Why did you only come now?

747
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:16,634
Why are you standing there?

748
00:37:17,535 --> 00:37:18,402
Come here.

749
00:37:22,473 --> 00:37:23,240
Don't move.

750
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:29,914
Does it hurt?

751
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:36,520
But definitely not as much as your heart hurts for me.

752
00:37:42,994 --> 00:37:44,395
Stop standing. Sit down.

753
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:49,767
I'm fine, bro.

754
00:37:50,034 --> 00:37:50,468
Sit.

755
00:37:58,843 --> 00:37:59,610
Don't worry.

756
00:38:00,044 --> 00:38:01,545
I've felt much better these past two days.

757
00:38:02,046 --> 00:38:02,913
Don't worry about me,

758
00:38:03,714 --> 00:38:05,149
and tell Mom and Dad not to worry either.

759
00:38:21,399 --> 00:38:22,667
In a few days,

760
00:38:23,167 --> 00:38:24,168
I'll be back on my feet again.

761
00:38:26,470 --> 00:38:28,105
Still joking at a time like this.

762
00:38:33,210 --> 00:38:34,145
Actually,

763
00:38:36,814 --> 00:38:37,648
I've been outside the whole time.

764
00:38:39,784 --> 00:38:41,252
I just didn't have the courage to come in.

765
00:38:42,486 --> 00:38:43,554
I knew you were outside.

766
00:38:45,623 --> 00:38:47,825
My favorite West Lake beef soup,

767
00:38:48,793 --> 00:38:50,161
without a single shred of wood ear.

768
00:38:51,295 --> 00:38:53,064
I knew it was specially made for me.

769
00:38:56,534 --> 00:38:57,368
I brought some today too.

770
00:38:58,035 --> 00:38:58,502
Have some.

771
00:38:59,570 --> 00:38:59,904
Okay.

772
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:14,485
What's wrong?

773
00:39:18,989 --> 00:39:19,890
Tangtang used to

774
00:39:20,624 --> 00:39:21,992
bring it to me.

775
00:39:26,564 --> 00:39:27,031
Don't, don't.

776
00:39:27,565 --> 00:39:28,833
Don't be sad.

777
00:39:29,934 --> 00:39:30,334
Bro,

778
00:39:33,070 --> 00:39:34,071
we broke up.

779
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:36,273
He left.

780
00:39:39,143 --> 00:39:40,311
I'll go find him right now.

781
00:39:40,911 --> 00:39:41,612
Don't.

782
00:39:43,748 --> 00:39:45,015
I was the one who proposed breaking up.

783
00:39:49,453 --> 00:39:51,255
I'm just a little sad.

784
00:39:52,690 --> 00:39:54,692
Let me cry for a while. I'll be fine.

785
00:40:11,675 --> 00:40:12,409
At present,

786
00:40:12,543 --> 00:40:13,544
the treatment is working very well.

787
00:40:14,211 --> 00:40:15,212
The thrombus has completely disappeared.

788
00:40:16,414 --> 00:40:17,815
The main reason is that you cooperated so well this time.

789
00:40:18,482 --> 00:40:19,483
Dr. Ye and the other nurses

790
00:40:19,550 --> 00:40:20,284
all praised you.

791
00:40:21,886 --> 00:40:23,487
This time, I'm determined to be

792
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:24,355
a model patient.

793
00:40:26,157 --> 00:40:26,957
The next issue to address

794
00:40:26,991 --> 00:40:28,292
is your atrial fibrillation.

795
00:40:28,993 --> 00:40:30,161
For that, we'll need

796
00:40:30,194 --> 00:40:31,362
catheter radiofrequency ablation

797
00:40:31,662 --> 00:40:32,863
to restore your heart

798
00:40:32,863 --> 00:40:33,731
to a normal rhythm.

799
00:40:34,331 --> 00:40:35,132
But considering

800
00:40:35,199 --> 00:40:36,600
that you've already developed a thrombus before,

801
00:40:36,867 --> 00:40:37,535
and that this time

802
00:40:37,601 --> 00:40:38,469
your cerebral MR angiography

803
00:40:38,669 --> 00:40:39,904
also found a three-millimeter

804
00:40:40,004 --> 00:40:40,871
intracranial aneurysm,

805
00:40:41,005 --> 00:40:42,273
Neurology said

806
00:40:42,706 --> 00:40:44,442
that because it's very small,

807
00:40:44,575 --> 00:40:45,376
we can simply monitor it.

808
00:40:45,709 --> 00:40:46,076
Right.

809
00:40:46,477 --> 00:40:47,311
The aneurysm itself

810
00:40:47,311 --> 00:40:48,212
doesn't require immediate treatment.

811
00:40:48,612 --> 00:40:49,847
But because it's there,

812
00:40:50,314 --> 00:40:51,282
long-term use of

813
00:40:51,415 --> 00:40:52,183
anticoagulants

814
00:40:52,483 --> 00:40:53,284
would carry a risk.

815
00:40:53,684 --> 00:40:54,919
So this time, I plan to arrange

816
00:40:54,985 --> 00:40:56,954
atrial fibrillation ablation

817
00:40:57,087 --> 00:40:58,322
plus left atrial appendage closure

818
00:40:58,456 --> 00:40:59,323
as a one-stop procedure.

819
00:41:00,624 --> 00:41:01,492
I understand atrial fibrillation,

820
00:41:01,826 --> 00:41:02,793
but what's the left atrial appendage?

821
00:41:05,162 --> 00:41:07,364
If we compare the heart to a house,

822
00:41:07,631 --> 00:41:08,465
the left atrial appendage

823
00:41:08,532 --> 00:41:09,834
is like a small side room.

824
00:41:10,334 --> 00:41:10,801
But

825
00:41:10,868 --> 00:41:11,936
this little room has

826
00:41:11,936 --> 00:41:12,837
an irregular shape.

827
00:41:13,103 --> 00:41:14,505
So when atrial fibrillation occurs,

828
00:41:14,605 --> 00:41:15,773
blood flow inside the left atrial appendage

829
00:41:15,773 --> 00:41:16,674
becomes very slow,

830
00:41:17,041 --> 00:41:18,442
making it easier for clots to form.

831
00:41:18,776 --> 00:41:19,944
That's called a left atrial appendage thrombus.

832
00:41:20,277 --> 00:41:20,911
These clots

833
00:41:20,911 --> 00:41:21,712
are often quite large.

834
00:41:21,912 --> 00:41:22,813
Once they break loose,

835
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:24,014
the bloodstream from your heart

836
00:41:24,081 --> 00:41:25,182
can carry them into the aorta.

837
00:41:25,449 --> 00:41:26,483
If they block a cerebral vessel,

838
00:41:26,684 --> 00:41:27,384
you'll have a stroke.

839
00:41:27,751 --> 00:41:28,786
If they block a coronary artery,

840
00:41:28,919 --> 00:41:29,587
you'll have a heart attack.

841
00:41:30,187 --> 00:41:31,188
So my previous stroke

842
00:41:31,322 --> 00:41:31,989
was caused by this?

843
00:41:32,623 --> 00:41:33,023
Yes.

844
00:41:33,424 --> 00:41:34,992
The left atrial appendage closure

845
00:41:35,125 --> 00:41:36,227
Director Zhou plans to perform

846
00:41:36,427 --> 00:41:37,828
uses an occluder device

847
00:41:38,095 --> 00:41:39,730
to seal off the appendage.

848
00:41:40,197 --> 00:41:41,765
In other words, it closes

849
00:41:41,799 --> 00:41:42,433
that small side room,

850
00:41:42,967 --> 00:41:44,168
preventing clots

851
00:41:44,201 --> 00:41:45,603
from escaping again

852
00:41:45,870 --> 00:41:47,171
and lowering your risk of another stroke.

853
00:41:48,706 --> 00:41:50,407
So this procedure

854
00:41:50,574 --> 00:41:51,509
can solve both of my problems

855
00:41:51,509 --> 00:41:52,443
at the same time.

856
00:41:53,444 --> 00:41:54,111
Director Xiaofeng,

857
00:41:54,211 --> 00:41:55,012
you're amazing.

858
00:41:56,547 --> 00:41:57,548
Where do I sign?

859
00:41:58,649 --> 00:41:59,917
Don't you have any other questions?

860
00:42:00,084 --> 00:42:00,718
No.

861
00:42:01,252 --> 00:42:02,553
Just do whatever you think is best.

862
00:42:03,087 --> 00:42:03,654
I trust you.

863
00:42:06,724 --> 00:42:07,758
If every patient

864
00:42:07,925 --> 00:42:09,326
were as compliant

865
00:42:09,527 --> 00:42:10,160
and trusting as you,

866
00:42:10,728 --> 00:42:11,362
our work

867
00:42:11,428 --> 00:42:12,329
would go much more smoothly.

868
00:42:12,830 --> 00:42:13,731
Dr. Ye,

869
00:42:14,031 --> 00:42:15,566
you didn't see me

870
00:42:15,833 --> 00:42:16,734
when I was not compliant.

871
00:42:17,768 --> 00:42:19,103
A model patient

872
00:42:19,436 --> 00:42:20,437
should get a little red flower.

873
00:42:22,773 --> 00:42:23,374
Thank you.

874
00:42:38,923 --> 00:42:39,390
Qiangwei,

875
00:42:40,324 --> 00:42:41,191
Director Guo will first

876
00:42:41,292 --> 00:42:42,159
perform the

877
00:42:42,159 --> 00:42:43,227
radiofrequency ablation.

878
00:42:43,627 --> 00:42:44,495
Then I'll take over

879
00:42:44,528 --> 00:42:45,829
and perform the left atrial appendage closure.

880
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:47,731
I'll be here the whole time.

881
00:42:47,998 --> 00:42:48,365
Okay.

882
00:42:49,199 --> 00:42:49,800
Don't worry.

883
00:42:49,967 --> 00:42:50,367
It'll be fine.

884
00:42:51,368 --> 00:42:51,802
Director Guo.

885
00:42:52,503 --> 00:42:52,870
Director Guo.

